# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# pi-setup / POS — top-level Python dependencies (source of truth).
#
# Edit THIS file, then regenerate the fully pinned + hashed lockfile with:
#
#     ./scripts/lock-python-deps.sh pi-setup
#
# That script runs `uv pip compile --generate-hashes` against the Pi 5's
# aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu target, so the resolved wheels match what gets
# installed on the Pi (regardless of the host arch you regenerate from).
# The Dockerfile installs from `requirements.txt` with
# `pip install --require-hashes`, so any drift will fail the build loudly.
#
# Direct git+ URLs (currently just the OpenAI CLIP repo) cannot be hashed by
# uv pip compile and live in `requirements-vcs.txt` instead — that file pins
# the exact commit SHA, which IS itself a content hash, so reproducibility
# is preserved.
#
# See `docs/REPRODUCIBILITY.md` for the full bump procedure.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

