# CLIP + FAISS — visual card identification engine.
# Use standard PyPI torch wheels — they include ARM64 (Pi 5) builds.
# Do NOT add --extra-index-url pytorch whl/cpu here; those are x86-only.
# NOTE: `clip` itself lives in `requirements-vcs.txt` (git+ URL, no hash).
#
# torch is capped at <2.11 because torch 2.11 dropped the
# `platform_machine == "x86_64"` markers on its nvidia-* CUDA deps and
# instead just gates them on `platform_system == "Linux"` — which matches
# aarch64 Linux on the Pi 5 too. Those nvidia-* packages have no aarch64
# wheels on PyPI, so a torch>=2.11 lockfile won't install on the Pi at
# all. 2.10.x still has the proper x86_64-only marker. Bump the cap when
# upstream torch fixes that on Linux/aarch64 — see
# `docs/REPRODUCIBILITY.md` for the procedure.
torch>=2.6,<2.11
torchvision>=0.21,<0.26
faiss-cpu>=1.7.4
